properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 24 at 4:01PM HST until January 26 at 6:00AM HST by NWS Honolulu HI
properties.description:
* WHAT...Seas 8 to 13 feet expected. Northeast to east winds 10 to
20 knots, except Alenuihaha Channel northeast winds 15 to 25
knots.

* WHERE...Oahu Leeward Waters, Kaiwi Channel, Maui County
Windward Waters, Maui County Leeward Waters, Pailolo Channel,
Alenuihaha Channel, Big Island Windward Waters, Big Island
Leeward Waters and Big Island Southeast Waters.

* WHEN...From 6 AM Saturday to 6 AM HST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
A Small Craft Advisory means that wind speeds of 25 to 33 knots
and/or seas 10 feet or greater are expected to produce conditions
hazardous to small craft. Inexperienced mariners, especially
those operating smaller vessels, should avoid navigating in these
conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM SATURDAY TO 6 AM HST SUNDAY
